here's a summary of our views on quantum.  We've spoken to the $QUBT CEO Robert Liscouski a couple times & also to the head of $AMZN AWS Braket
column3: Robert Moulds.  We think quantum computing holds a whole lot of promise because it can in principle solve certain kinds of mathematical problems faster than binary machines.  The technology is very
column4: very early stage & it is unclear whether either tech or commercial advantage will materialize at scale.  It might
column6: it's just too early to say.  It is however in our view a prime time in high end computing for a paradigm shift.  The last couple decades have been characterized by x86 and Linux making inroads into the datacenter
column8: but cost alone isn't a paradigm shift.    We're excited about quantum and own suitably modest allocations in both QUBT and DMYI.
